<HEAD>Eds: Also in Tuesday AMs report.</HEAD>
<HEAD>An AP Extra</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDITOR'S NOTE </NOTE>
<TEXT>
   The furor over <PERSON>Salman Rushdie</PERSON>'s novel ``The
Satanic Verses'' highlights a gulf between <LOCATION>Western Europe</LOCATION> and its
Moslem minorities. Here is a report from an English city with a
large Moslem community.
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>By MAUREEN JOHNSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BRADFORD, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The furor over <PERSON>Salman Rushdie</PERSON>'s novel ``The
Satanic Verses'' highlights a gulf between <LOCATION>Western Europe</LOCATION> and its
Moslem minorities. Here is a report from an English city with a
large Moslem community.
</TEXT>
